    "DCs can also control how much energy they use; reducing this lowers their energy costs and carbon footprint.",
    "For instance, a data center may use either traditional resources, such as the electricity grid, single or combination of green energy sources, such as solar panels and wind turbines.",
    "Additionally, data centers may also have installed diesel generators to address power outages and anomalies.",
    "Another important component within this environment is the cloud user, who submits service requests in the form of several parameters such as instance type, storage, reservation time, start-time, end-time, etc.",
    "The core of cloud computing lies in the principle of on-demand resource provisioning."
